<br>
Take your complaints about rodding to your guild officer or raid leader, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>not</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/Spells/Shock_of_Fiery_Blades.htm">Shock of Fiery Blades</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> is so good it's ridiculous.  No, I don't mean its ratio or anything, but it is a fire based conjuration shock.  No tricky LOS issues like a bolt, and we all know fire is a better nuke than magic.  The spell is practically a no-brainer.  When fire nukes are appropriate, which is most of the time, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Shock of Fiery Blades</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/Spells/Transons_Phantasmal_Protection.htm">Transon's Phantasmal Protection</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> is another sweet spell.  A componentless upgrade to the phantasmal armor series with mana regeneration?  Its only fault is that it does not stack with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Protection of the Grove</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and in any case, with hitpoint regeneration now translated into mana regeneration, PotG/PotC is only one and third mana per tick better mana regeneration than TPP.  This is significant.<br>
<br>
The two pet heals, of which I only have TEI, are both significant. Prior to <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/Spells/Transons_Elemental_Infusion.htm">Transon's Elemental Infusion</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, the next best pet heal would be the 20th level spell <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/Spells/Renew_Summoning.htm">Renew Summoning</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  Comparing the two, TEI heals over two and half times the damage in nearly the same amount of time and is conjuration based?  How is this <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>not</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> a major upgrade of the spell?<br>
<br>
And no, mages are definitely <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>not</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> the masters of healing their pets, we never were.  That distinction now clearly belongs to beastlords.<br>
<br>
How long have mages been asking for improved invisibility?  We got <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/Spells/Veil_of_Elements.htm">Veil of Elements</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, which many thought we would <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>never</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> get because of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Call of the Hero</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Focus items</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> were announced as part of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Luclin</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and delivered very late.  They gave cheap and immediate access to all mages to nearly all the good focus effects except mana preservation and extended range.  Many mages still use the summoned items.  For those who respond <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;Whoopee!  More crap to summon!&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, I respond <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;Oh boy!  More buffs to cast!  More heals to toss!&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  Nearly every caster class has their share of stupid boring spell casts in support of the group or the raid.  Suck it up, soldier, and stop complaining.  We do need some kind of drop or auto drop command to be sure.<br>
<br>
The AA abilities are better than many mages are willing to admit.  The archetypes are solid, and benefit mages strongly, and the class skills, while not as good as Ranger or Wizard, are better than most other classes.  I have 80 AA, and I don't regret a single one of them.<br>
<br>
And while the recent batch of pet upgrades in theory benefited all pet owners, in practice, mages benefited far more than other pet classes.  Warders <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>still</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> suck, and necromancers were never as dependent on their pets as we are.  Neutral pets opened up many encounters, making mage + pet the norm, instead of the exception.  The upgrades to the epic and the greater vocarates were significant, and matter much more to mages than the upgrades for necromancers.  For all other pet classes, the improvements had marginal effects.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Cyricus:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Chaincast usually means death. Need some kind of aggro reduction spell then...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->You don't actually chain pets, do you?  I do.<br>
<br>
With the new resist rules, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Malosini</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> can have a profound effect on resists.  I always pull with this spell soloing.  Encounters vary, but almost always when I chain pets, I can chain cast <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Boots of Bladecaling</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> while the pet is fighting, and still keep the mob on the next pet.  Often, in order to speed things up, I can alternate boots with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Wrath of Elements</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Now that I have <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Spell Casting Subtlety 3</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, I find I can alternate boots and rains and still chain pets.  I chain cast all day long, pushing aggro as hard as I can, and I never die.<br>
<br>
Aggro management is not difficult for mages, and never has been.  We are usually among the last to get aggro in a group or especially on a raid.  We do not need any more tools for aggro management than we have already been provided with.<br>
<br>
Yes, SoL and post-SoL, we mages did indeed <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;make out like bandits.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  We are back near the top of the heap where we ought to have been before.  We crank out serious damage, as was intended.<br>
<br>
PoP looks to me like it will turn out well enough for mages.  If the new pets are fine, and the damage spells are tweaked a bit, I will have few complaints, which I have enumerated elsewhere.<br>
<br>
I have not felt this good about being a mage since Kunark.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Sage ArchMage Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
