_______________________________________<br>
Why? because reclaiming a pet and casting a new one is infinately more mana efficient then healing a pet. You can heal a pet a little bit, for a large mana cost, or you can reclaim your near-death pet and summon a new one and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> gain mana</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> in the process. Hopefully nothing you're trying to solo will kill your pet faster than you can click velious legs. Your pet will be buffless for a few seconds.<br>
<br>
The summed mez will be pretty helpful with improved reclaim I think, assuming there's enough summoned mobs to kill. IRE your pet at like 4% health and mez the mob, summon a new pet and use clicky buffs. You can fight all day in that case.<br>
<br>
______________________________________________<br>
Mend companion? Other classes get this as a regular heal instead of having to put AA's into it...and theres is not a refresh time on it<br>
______________________________________________<br>
<br>
I'm not sure where you're getting this info. My best guess is that you were looking for something negative to say about something, and since that one didn't look particularly great to you, you made something up hoping no one would notice.  As far as I can tell, the only class that gets a pet heal that comes even close is beastlords (unless you want to count a shaman, but those pets aren't even close to comparable).  Necro's don't get any heal spell that good. Their 1000pt pet heal takes 500 of their own health.   <br>
<br>
But that doesn't matter, either. Yes, it's nice to be able to heal a pet you gave weapons and armor to, and buffed up, but just because you CAN give your pet weapons, doesn't mean it's the most efficient way of doing things. Like a few have said, mages aren't the best pet healers. I would have to agree that that is a beastlord's thing now.<br>
<br>
__________________________________________<br>
Mass Group Buff? Im no Shaman..what group buffs<br>
__________________________________________<br>
I totally agree here, weird...<br>
<br>
__________________________________________<br>
Quick Summoning? Nice..but would be better if they also worked on our DD spells<br>
__________________________________________<br>
I'm thinking you need some new tactics. Making a single pet and nuking/healing isn't what works anymore. That was good for level 20-50ish, but it doesn't cut it anymore. I think that yanbun was inferring that the new pets would at least be comparable to epic, so you can feel free to reclaim-cann. Quick summoning helps out tremendously there.<br>
<br>
Not to mention chain summonig.  When you got a mob coming after you, you want to be able to cast a pet as fast as possible so you can regain concentration.<br>
<br>
Yes, it would be nice if it worked on nukes, but it's MUCH more helpful on pets.<br>
___________________________________________<br>
Turn Summoned? Where are the summoned mobs? None right now, so dont say wait for POP<br>
___________________________________________<br>
<br>
Wait for PoP.  If i'm not mistaken, there's a few planes that are element-based, and it stands to reason that there will be a lot of summoned mobs. This also applies to the new charm and mez summoned spells.  If there aren't, then you have a legitamate complaint.<br>
<br>
As for right now, I can agree. Not just that the summoned mobs are scarce to say the least, but if i have a bunch of summoned mobs on me in the hole, the last thing I want to do is fear them to get more.  about the only thing I can see this helping with is getting a chance to gate while in the hole.<br>
_____________________________________________<br>
<br>
Please tell me where and what is good. No one likes there Class AA's. My RL brother (60 Wizard) even talks about how Magicians got screwed on there class AAs. We got hand me downs from other people regular spells or things that we dont use.<br>
_____________________________________________<br>
It's their, but I don't want to talk about grammar (especially since I make a few mistakes here and there myself) but I figured in case you didn't know, now you do.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I agree that we got a few AA skills that, to put nicely, suck, but we can't compare our aa skills to manaburn and DC. Yes, those are nice, but we're not the only ones screwed out of decent class AA skills. Rogues have it just as bad, and i'm sure a few others as well.  DC for druids and necros is borderline worthless, and even the chanter DC is pretty limited.<br>
____________________________________________<br>
Im sorry, you can be a &quot;Verant Poster Boy&quot; but what we got needs to be REVAMPED.<br>
____________________________________________<br>
<br>
I'm sorry, but not everything we have needs to be revamped. <br>
<br>
And I don't see how raz is a &quot;verant poster boy.&quot; you think because he uses correct grammar and makes his thoughts clear he's a poster-boy? Maybe it's because his view differs from yours. I've never heard raz say that verant is perfect.<br>
<br>
I think instead of trying to find something negative to say about everything, try out different tactics and play the game. Evolve. Mages have improved by leaps and bounds since luclin came out, you're just not seeing it.<br>
